                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2536: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-09T08:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 9, 1931—8 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 9—1:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>889. Following from Consul General at Mukden, November 8, 11 p.m.: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Local Peace Maintenance Committee issued proclamation yesterday to the
                            effect that it is functioning as the Provincial Government during this
                            transitional period, that it does not concern itself with either past or
                            future questions, and that it has no connection with <pb facs="0504"
                                n="394" xml:id="pg_394"/> Nanking or Marshal Chang. All bureaus and
                            administrative offices are directed to observe the laws and carry out
                            instructions.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated to Shanghai.</p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
